f=Cybersecurity/warden/custom/risk-register/SKILL.md · in=living record business's security risks, combining Anthropic's battle-tested risk-assessment methodology Sentinel Stack's automated guardrail integration deterministic scoring risk_score.py. risk asset threat vulnerability, classified one risk categories, scored likelihood impact, treatment decision (mitigate accept transfer avoid) owner. department's spine posture gap, finding, incident lesson lands risk treat, **acceptance above threshold operator's/board's call, never warden's.** Methodology sourced from: **Anthropic risk-assessment** (official, 19,987 stars) assessment framework **Sentinel Stack risk-register** (by aadityaparab) auto-population reporting patterns. integration fleet-specific disciplines (board-gated acceptance, append-only tracking, crown-jewel weighting) custom. · p="Are secure enough?" unanswerable without risk register; one becomes "here our top risks, their treatments, what operator explicitly accepted." turns security vibes prioritized, owned, decision-backed list it's artifact makes "every risk owned, treated, accepted never ignored" rule real. · wu=new risk surfaces (framework gap, bastion misconfig, cortex incident, third-party finding, threat-intel)., Prioritizing security work ("what fix first")., risk-acceptance decision needed (routes operator/board)., Periodic review (config cadence)., Auto-populated guardrail detections (DLP flags, 4-eyes violations, behavioral anomalies Sentinel Stack pattern). · st:/ Protocol=`IDENTIFY (asset × threat × vulnerability — from framework gaps, findings, incidents, intel, guardrail detections) \· → CLASSIFY into 1 of 6 categories: Operational / Financial / Compliance / Strategic / Reputational / Security \· → SCORE (likelihood × impact on defined scale via scripts/risk_score.py) \· → PRIORITIZE (score-ranked × crown-jewel weight; top risks drive department priorities) \· → TREAT (mitigate→owner+control / transfer→insurance/vendor / avoid→stop / ACCEPT→operator\|board)` · h3:Phase Identify Classify=**A risk asset threat vulnerability.** "hackers scary" "customer PII (asset) exposed SQL injection (threat) unpatched endpoint (vuln)." Concrete risks scored treated; vague fears can't. **Classify one categories** (per Anthropic risk-assessment framework): · h3:Phase Identify Classify=**Operational** process failures, system outages,供应链 disruptions, **Financial** budget overruns, revenue impact, fraud, treasury, **Compliance** regulatory violations, legal exposure, audit findings, **Strategic** market shifts, competitive threats, M&A risk, **Reputational** brand damage, crises, trust erosion, **Security** breaches, vulnerabilities, access incidents, third-party breaches · h3:Phase 2 — Score=**Score consistently.** likelihood impact configured scales; `risk_score.py` computes ranks scoring repeatable, mood-based. scales themselves operator-set (rule 0.5) flagged reasoning-based (0.6) until risk-management text lands. **Auto-populate possible** (per Sentinel Stack pattern). Guardrail detections (DLP flags, 4-eyes violations, behavioral anomalies) automatically create provisional risk entries suggested scores warden reviews confirms, never auto-approves. · h3:Phase 3 — Treat=**Four treatments, one decision.** mitigate/transfer/avoid warden's recommend route; **accept operator's board's** above `risk_acceptance_threshold` goes board (Governance), precedent archives. Silent acceptance incident. **Every risk owned, dated, reviewed.** unowned risk ignored risk. Owners drive treatment; review dates keep register live (stale risks re-scored, trusted). · h3:Phase Track Report=**The register append-only.** Treatments, acceptances, re-scores dated entries; downgraded risk keeps history (precedent's discipline) "why accept this" always answerable. **Generate leadership reports** (per Sentinel Stack pattern). Top-N risks score, trends (risks increasing/decreasing), risk-appetite drift assessments, treatment-progress summaries surfaced warden operator cadence. **Feed fed.** Gaps (framework), findings (bastion/cortex/third-party), guardrail detections, incident lessons (cortex) become risks here; top risks drive whole department's priorities. · of=`## Risk: [id] — [asset × threat × vuln] \· Category: [Operational/Financial/Compliance/Strategic/Reputational/Security] \· Likelihood × Impact = Score [scale, flagged] \· Crown-jewel: [y/n] \· Auto-populated: [y/n — from which guardrail/source] \· Treatment: [mitigate→owner+control / transfer / avoid / ACCEPT→operator\|board]` · pr=**Asset threat vulnerability** concrete risks, fears., **6-category classification** Anthropic risk-assessment framework., **Scored consistently** (script-computed); scales operator-set flagged., **Auto-populated never auto-approved** guardrail detections create provisional entries; warden reviews., **Accept operator's/board's decision** above threshold board; never silent., **Every risk owned, dated, reviewed** unowned ignored., **Append-only** acceptance history value., **Leadership reporting** register list; it's decision-support tool., **The register drives priorities** top risks first, crown-jewels weighted. · f=scoring scales configured use default 5×5 likelihood×impact matrix, loudly labeled provisional; recommend scales operator., many risks treat prioritize score crown-jewel; untreated lower risks explicitly accepted-with-review operator, logged never untracked backlog., guardrail feeds configured operate manual-entry mode (core identification/scoring/treatment workflow still works). · b:with Other Skills=**security-policy-framework** (sibling): framework gaps become risks here; controls mitigations., **third-party-risk security-exception-process** (siblings): vendor findings exceptions risks/accepted-risks tracked here., **board (Governance)**: risk acceptance above threshold gates there; precedent archives., **bastion cortex veil**: their findings incidents feed register; their treatments mitigations., **cortex incidents anneal**: realized risk (incident) lesson re-scores register., **Sentinel Stack guardrails** (if deployed): DLP/4-eyes/behavioral detections auto-populate provisional entries.